fields.name: Amber Patchouli and Lavender Fragrance 50ml
fields.description: This warm, earthy, sensual fragrance is popular with both male and female customers. Prepared from from herbal resins, oils and other natural plant extracts, it includes rock rose, patchouli bark, benzoin and tonka beans. It has taken a long time to perfect the recipe for this fragrance and we feel really happy with it. We are currently working on our new one... watch this space!
fields.directions: Spray freely onto skin and clothing as desired.  The fragrance is flammable so please avoid naked flames .
fields.ingredients: Natural herbal resins, gums, oils and other extracts (including a natural source of coumarin), perfumer's alcohol (ethanol, monopropylene glycol, isopropyl myristate).

fields.name: Rosehip Syrup 200ml
fields.description:
This syrup is prepared from hand-picked wild rosehips, combined with freshly squeezed lemon juice and unrefined sugar. It provides a fantastically rich source of vitamin C. We find it a wonderful tonic for the dark winter months, when our immunity can be lower  and our exposure to the sunshine is reduced.

Rosehip syrup has long been used  to help the body deal with  infections and to maintain health and vitality.
fields.directions:
The syrup can be taken straight off the spoon or  added to hot water to make a warming drink. It is also delicious poured on porridge or ice cream for a treat.

We recommend 10ml each day during the winter, and double this dose when feeling ill or run down.

fields.name: Elderberry Syrup 200ml
fields.description: This warming, fruity syrup is made to a traditional recipe containing wild elderberries, grated ginger root and freshly squeezed lemon juice.  Elderberries have a wonderful reputation for boosting immunity and helping with coughs, colds, flu and chest infections.
fields.directions: Best taken as a hot drink, but also delicious drizzled on porridge or ice cream! We would recommend 10ml taken 2 - 3 times daily if you have symptoms of a cold, flu or chest infection or 10ml once daily for general winter support.

fields.name: Muscle and Joint Cream 60ml
fields.description: Our muscle and joint cream contains a warming blend of herbal extracts traditionally used to help ease pain, stiffness and  inflammation in the  joints and  muscles. The cream base is  simple, vegan and organic.  We have found that the cream benefits people with arthritis, rheumatism , sprains, bruising and general stiffness in the joints.
fields.directions: Massage into affected areas 2- 3 times daily. N.B. As the cream contains capsicum it is important to avoid the eyes and to wash the hands after applying.
fields.ingredients: ginger, wintergreen, capsicum minimum, camphor, cinnamon, water, emulsifying wax, stearyl alcohol, coconut oil, cocoa butter, tween, vitamin E, glycerine

fields.name: Midge and Mosquito Repellent 60ml
fields.description: Our midge and mosquito repellant  has evolved over many years of trial and error. Loyal customers now choose this over anything else, in the knowledge that it not only helps to deter midges and mosquitos, but also contains no irritating and potentially harmful chemicals. The cream contains a blend of herbal extracts  including bog myrtle, eucalyptus, citronella and rosemary
fields.directions: Apply  to  exposed areas as needed, avoiding the eyes. We recommend applying to a small area of skin initially to ensure you are not sensitive to any of the oils.
fields.ingredients: bog myrtle extract, eucalyptus oil, citronella oil, rosemary oil, water, emulsifying wax, stearyl alcohol, coconut oil, cocoa butter, tween, vitamin E, glycerine

fields.name: Neroli Face and Body Cream 60ml
fields.description: A naturally fragranced, luxurious, organic and vegan face cream with aloe vera, geranium, witch hazel, neroli, and lavender. Ideal for normal to dry skin, this is one of our most popular products.
fields.directions: Massage gently onto face and neck morning and night after thorough cleansing.
fields.ingredients: neroli oil, witch hazel water, geranium oil, lavender oil, water, emulsifying wax, stearyl alcohol, coconut oil, cocoa butter, tween, vitamin E, glycerine.

fields.name: Frankincense Face Cream 60ml
fields.description: An exotic blend of herbal extracts and oils carefully chosen to nourish and tone normal to combination skin. This popular cream contains extracts  of frankincense, aloe vera, marshmallow root  and calendula flowers.  Loyal customers tell us that they choose this over and above other more expensive creams, because of its pure, natural ingredients and therapeutic qualities. This cream is suitable for vegans.
fields.directions: Massage gently onto face and neck morning and night, after thorough cleansing.
fields.ingredients: frankincense oil, calendula extract, marshmallow root extract, aloe vera, witch hazel, water, emulsifying wax, stearyl alcohol, coconut oil, cocoa butter, tween, vitamin E, glycerine

fields.name: Herbal Balm 60ml
fields.description: This is a  wonderfully healing herbal ointment containing freshly harvested comfrey leaves,  marigold flowers and lavender and is a must for the first aid cabinet.
fields.directions: We would highly recommend this ointment for cracked skin (hands, feet, lips), bruising, sprains, minor burns and as a simple barrier ointment to help prevent  nappy rash. Apply as needed - a little goes a long way!
fields.ingredients: comfrey leaves (Symphytum officinalis), calendula flowers (Calendula officinalis), lavender flowers (Lavandula officinalis), sunflower oil, beeswax

fields.name: Clarity Blend 50g
fields.description: A delicious loose leaf blend of lemon balm, red sage and lemon verbena. Modern research confirms that these  herbs can help  improve memory and enhance mental clarity. This tea makes a refreshing and uplifting brew at any time of day.
fields.directions: Place 1 - 2 teaspoons per person in your teapot (you may wish to use an infuser ball or similar). Pour over freshly boiled water and infuse for 5-10 minutes. Pour out, straining if needed,  relax and enjoy!
fields.ingredients: sage (Salvia officinalis), lemon balm (Melissa officinalis), lemon verbena (Aloysia citrodora).

fields.name: Serenity Blend 50g
fields.description:
A soothing, gentle blend of chamomile and lavender flowers. These herbs are traditionally used to calm the nervous system in times of stress, to encourage  restful  sleep and to support good digestion. Lavender is  also used by herbalists to help treat mild depression.

This is the  perfect bedtime brew.
fields.directions: Place 1 - 2 teaspoons per person in your teapot (you may wish to use an infuser ball or similar). Pour over freshly boiled water and infuse for 5-10 minutes. Pour out, straining if needed, relax and enjoy!
fields.ingredients: chamomile flowers (Chamomilla recutita), lavender flowers (Lavandula officinalis).

fields.name: Digestive Blend 50g
fields.description:
A refreshing, tasty and soothing  tea, containing peppermint, fennel seed and rosemary. These herbs are known to improve digestion and to ease digestive discomfort, bloating and cramps.

This tea can be enjoyed after meals to aid digestion or at any time as a gentle digestive tonic.
fields.directions: Place 1 - 2 teaspoons per person in your teapot (you may wish to use an infuser ball or similar). Pour over freshly boiled water and infuse for 5-10 minutes. Pour out, straining if needed, relax and enjoy!
fields.ingredients: peppermint (Mentha piperita), fennel (Foeniculum vulgare), rosemary (Rosmarinus officinalis).

fields.name: Valerian Tincture 50 ml
fields.description: A herbal tincture prepared from organic valerian root. This is a tried and tested  herbal remedy traditionally used to promote restful sleep and  as  a relaxant in times of stress or anxiety. It can also be used  as  a  supportive nerve tonic. Valerian is a native herb that tends to grow in damp areas. The root has a distinctive smell .
fields.directions: For adults and children over 12 years, take 20 drops in a little hot water up to 3 times daily.
fields.ingredients: organic valerian root (Valeriana officinalis), ethanol and water

fields.name: Chest Tincture 50ml
fields.description: These herbs have been chosen and blended by our herbalist. Thyme is used to help clear infections and congested mucous in the lungs. Elderberry is often prescribed by herbalists to improve immune function and to help the body deal with viral and bacterial infections. Marshmallow is a gentle and soothing expectorant, which can also ease tickly coughs.
fields.directions: For adults and children over 12 years, take 20 drops in a little hot water up to 3 times daily.
fields.ingredients: organic thyme leaf (Thymus officinalis), organic elderberry (Sambucus nigra), organic marshmallow root (Althaea officinalis), water, ethanol.

fields.name: Echinacea Tincture 50ml
fields.description: Echinacea is traditionally used to support the immune system and is prescribed by herbalists to support the body to deal with with colds, flu,   and many other viral and bacterial  infections. This plant was originally a Native American medicine and is now widely prescribed by herbalists.
fields.directions: For adults and children over 12 years (seek guidance from a qualified herbalist for young infants), take 20 drops in a little hot water up to 3 times daily.
fields.ingredients: organic echinacea root (Echinacea angustifolia/purpurea), water, ethanol.

fields.name: Slippery Elm Powder 50g
fields.description: Slippery elm powder is used by herbalists to ease acid indigestion and inflammation of the digestive tract, and as a nourishing and strengthening remedy during convalescence. This powder is 100% pure and contains none of the additives sometimes found in other brands.
fields.directions: A soothing drink can be  prepared by mixing a teaspoon of slippery elm powder in half a mug of boiling water and whisking. When it cools a little, it slightly thickens . Honey can be added , though it has a pleasant taste.  Some people choose to add it to a smoothie, and in this case a teaspoon of powder is added to the other ingredients before blending.

fields.name: Golden Paste 190ml
fields.description:
Turmeric  has traditionally been considered an important medicinal herb with many health benefits. It is increasingly being tested scientifically and much of the research backs up the  traditional uses. 

 
Some of the benefits that have been supported in scientific studies   include:

    Use as an anti-oxidant and anti-inflammatory
    Reduction in joint inflammation
    May play a role in the prevention and treatment of cancer
    Reduction in cholesterol  levels
    May reduce the incidence of Alzheimers disease and other brain diseases,
    Possible benfits in the treatment of mild  depression

 

Contra indications – Turmeric is generally considered safe, however it is best avoided with blood thinning medication and if you have diabetes (as it can lower blood sugar). It may also slightly lower blood pressure.
fields.directions: Our Golden Paste is a combination of turmeric , coconut oil and black pepper. It can be used in cooking , mixed with youghurt or added to smoothies, We would suggest an initial dose of 1/2 teaspoon twice daily. Once opened it should be stored in the fridge and will keep for 2 weeks.
fields.ingredients: organic turmeric, organic coconut oil, black pepper, water
